					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If you use fractions of powers of 2 close to the numbers (1/2, 1/4, 1/8, 1/16, etc), you can do it much easier.
<br />
<br />For instance:
<br />damage = (STR*0.5) + (DEX*0.25) + (CON*0.125) + (A random from 0~5) 
<br />would be much easier to calculate since you can use right shifts instead of division.  But if you don't want DEX / 4 to be truncated, you need to use fixed point math.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Here come the fortune cookies!  Here come the fortune cookies!  They're wearing paper hats!</div>
